column5: We started out with a visit with the geese.Seen some ice build up.Nothing like Tinbangers.During our  drive this evening,I heard word of some changes going on,so we went for a drive, and seen some changes in the area. Cant say Im too impressed. We moved from the big city to get, what you would say a, natural living. Woods and wild life.Barrie sucks now.It,s just like the big city. Money grabb,n   .   Pay no mind to the women behind the camera.LOL

i have to agree, i'm not looking forward to the 4 lanes all the way from the T. to north bay. not gonna help any i dont think. it's hard on all the by passed small towns along the way and not gonna do nipissing any favours. other than the cost of land of course!
Pop and mudder are  in Katrine.Thier building the bridges as we speak.
Looks like you need it real bad Brian.To go fishing that is
out with the old in with the new....sign of progress Brian.....   Time to move farther I guess..   Smelts you say.....
you`re making me feel old....dang    but I know what you mean
I thought for second there you were gonna start with a rendition of koombaya!

The 400 extension past Waubushene was bad enough. A lot of good people had their lives and lifestyle turned upside down by that project. Killed a lot of the local colour, and the economy.  I'm still amazed they haven't torn out "Gasoline Alley" . There are a lot of dead businesses and derelict properties already on the stretch to Orillia
just think misfish 22 days till opener!
Not sure when you moved to Barrie Brian...but I thought it was too much like a city 25 years ago. To me any berg with over 5,000 people .... IS A CITY!
